cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for local feature extraction tasks such as camera calibration, Patchmatching, optical flow estimation, and stereo matching. These tasks are typically associated with computer vision (CV), which suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the efficiency of CNN-based feature extraction, which is a common concern in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions a speed benchmark, which suggests that it may fall under the cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper provides example code for Torch, a popular deep learning framework used in multimedia (MM) research, making cs.MM a possible sub-category as well.
